    "ideation": "The crayon is a personification of creative play and tactile effort. The performance treats the robot like a child sketching: the eyes follow the 'tip' of an imaginary drawing being made on the screen, while the mouth represents the physical texture of wax on paper. We start with a focused 'waxy' color and narrow eyes of concentration. As the 'drawing' starts, the gaze tracks a scribbling motion (back and forth, up and down). The mouth frequency increases to represent the friction and 'scritch-scratch' of the crayon tip. Finally, the crayon is lifted, and the face beams with the bright, messy satisfaction of a completed masterpiece.",
